Dim ActivePanel As Panel ' This variable stores the 'Active' or visible panel
' This routine is run when the graphic is displayed. This routine makes sure that the home panel is visible. ' It sets the active panel to the visible panel Private Sub Display_AnimationStart() On Error GoTo ErrHandler
TabPanelGrp_Home.Visible = True Set ActivePanel = Me.TabPanelGrp_Home
Exit Sub
ErrHandler: Application.LogDiagnosticsMessage "Error occurred in " & ThisDisplay.FullName & _ " Display_AnimationStart(). Error # " & Err.Number & ": " & Err.Description, ftDiagSeverityError End Sub
' This routine is called to change panels to the New Panel that is passed to it. If the passed New Panel ' is not the Avtive Panel, then the New Panel will be made visible; the current active panel will be made ' not visible; and finally, the New Panel becomes the Active Panel Private Sub ChangePanel(ByRef NewPanel As Panel) On Error GoTo ErrHandler
If (NewPanel <> ActivePanel) Then NewPanel.Visible = True ActivePanel.Visible = False Set ActivePanel = NewPanel End If
Exit Sub
ErrHandler: Application.LogDiagnosticsMessage "Error occurred in " & ThisDisplay.FullName & _ " ChangePanel(). Error # " & Err.Number & ": " & Err.Description, ftDiagSeverityError End Sub
' For each tab button, there is a routine which calls the routine ChangePanel, passing it the Panel ' associated with the button.
Private Sub TabButton_Home_Released() Call ChangePanel(Me.TabPanelGrp_Home) End Sub Private Sub TabButton_Connections_Released() Call ChangePanel(Me.TabPanelGrp_Connections) End Sub Private Sub TabButton_Memory_Released() Call ChangePanel(Me.TabPanelGrp_Memory) End Sub Private Sub TabButton_CPU_Released() Call ChangePanel(Me.TabPanelGrp_CPU) End Sub
